The paper deals with the problem of scheduling jobs on parallel machines, which is a classic problem in computer science and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The use of parallel schedules is a novel approach to the problem, which could also be of interest to researchers in distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also introduces new guessing schemes, which could be of interest to researchers in machine learning and optimization (cs.LG, cs.IT). Finally, the paper involves analyzing the competitiveness of algorithms, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC).
